snippet: The target is an apparent attempt to temper expectations that the nation’s economy will rebound to anything near the double-digit growth of recent decades.
abstract: Chinese Pres Xi Jinping says government has set target of 6.5 percent annual economic growth from 2016 to 2020; statement is meant to dispel any expectation that Chinese economy will approach double-digit annual growth it up until recently regularly experienced.

byline.contributor: Chris Buckley contributed reporting. Owen Guo and Mia Li contributed research.

lead_paragraph: The target is an apparent attempt to temper expectations that the nation’s economy will rebound to anything near the double-digit growth of recent decades.

headline.main: China Aims for 6.5% Economic Growth Over Next 5 Years, Xi Says
headline.print_headline: China Tempers Its Growth Expectations, to 6.5% a Year
